Section 1:
1 L.D. 1667
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 JUDICIARY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 661, L.D. 1667, “Resolve, to Allow
10 Hemphill Farms, Inc. to Sue the State”
11 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the 2nd paragraph in the 4th line (page 1, line 10 in
12 L.D.) by inserting after the following: "individuals" the following: ', except that the award
13 of damages resulting from a civil action authorized by this resolve may not exceed
14 $2,500,000'
15 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
16 section number to read consecutively.
17 SUMMARY
1188 This amendment authorizes damages up to $2,500,000 for the civil action authorized
1199 by this resolve.
2200 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
2211 (See attached)
Page 1 - 132LR1575(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
